{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-detail-js","path":"/post/how-to-create-multi-language-website-in-magento-2/","result":{"data":{"wpPost":{"title":"How to Create Multi-language Website in Magento 2","content":"\n<p>Greetings! Are you looking to expand your online business to a global level and seeking effective ways to reach a larger audience? If the answer is affirmative, then developing a multi-language website may prove to be a viable solution for you. This write-up will provide you with valuable insights and my personal experience on <strong><em>how to create multi-language website in Magento 2</em></strong>. Being a blogger and online business owner, I can relate to the challenges of designing a website that caters to a global audience. However, with the aid of Magento 2, I was able to develop a website that effortlessly supports multiple languages. Thus, if you are prepared to take your business to the next level and appeal to customers from different parts of the globe, continue reading!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to Create Multi-language Website in Magento 2:A Step-by-Step Tutorial</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Creating a multi-language website in Magento 2 with the steps outlined in <strong><em>How to Create Multi-language Website in Magento 2</em></strong> is an important step in catering to a global audience and increasing the chances of customers making a purchase. By providing customers with the option to browse your website in their native language, you can create a more user-friendly and seamless browsing experience, ultimately leading to increased sales and customer satisfaction. In this guide, we will walk you through the steps of setting up a multi-language website in Magento 2.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 1: Install the Language Pack</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step in creating a multi-language website in Magento 2 is to install the language pack. You can do this by going to the <a href=\"https://marketplace.magento.com/\">Magento Marketplace</a> and searching for the language pack that you want to install. Once you have found the language pack, click the “Download” button and then follow the installation instructions.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 2: Create a Store View for Each Language</h2>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained wp-image-1396 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\"><div style=\"max-width:645px;display:block\"><img alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20height=&#x27;258&#x27;%20width=&#x27;645&#x27;%20xmlns=&#x27;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#x27;%20version=&#x27;1.1&#x27;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" style=\"max-width:100%;display:block;position:static\"/></div><div aria-hidden=\"true\" data-placeholder-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;width:100%\"></div><img data-gatsby-image-ssr=\"\" data-wp-inline-image=\"1\" data-main-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;transform:translateZ(0);transition:opacity 250ms linear;width:100%;will-change:opacity;opacity:0\" sizes=\"(min-width: 645px) 645px, 100vw\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" data-src=\"/_gatsby/image/8ab0ad8e3a7c364109f80618dd609874/5d5215f8177f9255e3223396a5f57ad9/How-to-Create-Multi-language-Website-in-Magento-2-01.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Create-Multi-language-Website-in-Magento-2-01.png&amp;a=w%3D161%26h%3D64%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-03-14T04%3A17%3A34\" data-srcset=\"/_gatsby/image/8ab0ad8e3a7c364109f80618dd609874/5d5215f8177f9255e3223396a5f57ad9/How-to-Create-Multi-language-Website-in-Magento-2-01.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Create-Multi-language-Websi