ento-2-01.png&a=w%3D161%26h%3D64%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-14T04%3A17%3A34 161w,/_gatsby/image/8ab0ad8e3a7c364109f80618dd609874/1f90034844335fa0c6167fc3fa5dc767/How-to-Create-Multi-language-Website-in-Magento-2-01.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Create-Multi-language-Website-in-Magento-2-01.png&a=w%3D323%26h%3D129%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-14T04%3A17%3A34 323w,/_gatsby/image/8ab0ad8e3a7c364109f80618dd609874/0126bebbcb68354454883e4b415b1713/How-to-Create-Multi-language-Website-in-Magento-2-01.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Create-Multi-language-Website-in-Magento-2-01.png&a=w%3D645%26h%3D258%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-14T04%3A17%3A34 645w\",\"sizes\":\"(min-width: 645px) 645px, 100vw\"}},\"layout\":\"constrained\",\"width\":645,\"height\":258},\"alt\":\"How to Create Multi-language Website in Magento 2 01\",\"className\":\"wp-image-1396 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\",\"data-wp-inline-image\":\"1\"}</script></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Once the language pack is installed, you will need to create a store view for each language that you want to support. To do this, go to the “Stores” menu and select “All Stores”. Here, you can create a new store view by clicking the “Create Store View” button. Enter a name for the store view, select the language that you want to use, and then click the “Save Store View” button.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 3: Translate the Text</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained wp-image-1401 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\"><div style=\"max-width:701px;display:block\"><img alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20height=&#x27;237&#x27;%20width=&#x27;701&#x27;%20xmlns=&#x27;http://www.w3